@startuml mesmerize-sqs-messaging-overview
title Mesmerize — SQS / REST Communication Overview\nADR-014 · Edge REST · Internal REST or SQS by matrix\nPatterns: Request/Reply · Correlation ID · Fire-and-forget · Content Enricher · DLQ

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Clinician / Device" as Client
rectangle "API Gateway / Edge" as GW #E3F2FD

rectangle "Service A\n(e.g. session / content)" as A #B3D4FC
rectangle "Service B\n(e.g. billing-evidence)" as B #B3D4FC
rectangle "Service C\n(e.g. engagement / audit)" as C #B3D4FC

queue "B.requests" as BREQ #FFF3E0
queue "B.replies" as BREP #FFF3E0
queue "C.events" as CEVT #E8F5E9
queue "*.dlq" as DLQ #FFCDD2

Client --> GW : REST (interactive)
GW --> A : REST
A --> B : REST\n(when simple sync OK)
A --> BREQ : SQS Request/Reply\n(correlationId + replyTo)
BREP --> A : Reply matched by\ncorrelationId
A --> CEVT : Fire-and-forget\n(async fact)
BREQ --> B
B --> BREP : Reply
CEVT --> C
BREQ ..> DLQ : after enrich +\nmax receives
CEVT ..> DLQ : after enrich +\nmax receives

legend right
  |= Pattern |= Use |
  | REST | Edge + optional internal sync |
  | Request/Reply | Internal wait-for-result |
  | Correlation ID | Match request ↔ reply |
  | Fire-and-forget | Async facts |
  | Content Enricher + DLQ | Error / poison path |
endlegend

@enduml
